news.title: Geo-mapping of houses in municipal areas on cards: Goa minister
news.para: Rane said that this exercise would be only so that civic bodies have live records available to them. People need not to worry because it would not increase any tax.

news.title: Four illegal colonies in Greater Noida demolished
news.para: The action was carried out by the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) on instructions of its CEO Surendra Singh, the officials said.

news.title: Dozens of landmark buildings under redevelopment in Ahmedabad
news.para: While Ahmedabad is expanding across its length and breadth with new projects being launched in most areas, areas such as Navrangpura, Vastrapur, Paldi, Vasna and Shahibaug – which are replete with key residential and commercial buildings – are increasingly witnessing redevelopment schemes and buyouts.

news.title: Bihar officers to face action if 5.51 lakh PMAY-G houses not completed by June
news.para: "The non-completion of construction of 5,51,893 houses -- 2,42,803 under PMAY-G and 3,09,090 under the erstwhile Indira Awas Yojana (IAY) - in rural areas of the state is a matter of grave concern.

news.title: Real estate arm of Morphogenesis to invest Rs 100 crore for office space project in Delhi
news.para: The company, through a joint development model, has developed 50,000 sq ft of office space and plan to take 4-5 similar projects in the micro markets.

news.title: RERA tells Delhi corporations not to approve unregistered building plans
news.para: The decision came only days after the authority made it essential for builders to register projects with a total developed area of more than 500 square metres, regardless of the number of flats constructed on it.

news.title: Delhi HC quashes mandatory RERA nod for construction
news.para: HC pointed out that the suo moto proceedings by the tribunal “practically injuncted all construction activity in the NCT of Delhi.”

news.title: For contempt of court, SC awards Nirmal Infrastructure's director seven days' jail
news.para: The HC had directed him to deposit a certain amount following an arbitral award of Rs 78 crore against him and Nirmal Infrastructure Pvt Ltd of which he is a director, in a commercial dispute with Urban Infrastructure Real Estate Fund over a share purchase agreement.

news.title: EOW arrests ex-CMD & director of AMR Infrastructures in Rs 600 crore scam
news.para: The two were declared proclaimed offenders on March 16, 2018. Over 3,000 people had invested in their projects for residential and commercial spaces. EOW had received around 650 complaints from investors duped by them. The accused are in police custody till Friday.

news.title: I-T department searches premises of Asian Granito, associate entities in Gujarat
news.para: ​​Residential properties of Asian Granito's Chairman and Managing Director Kamlesh Patel and other promoters were searched, he said.

news.title: SC sets aside HC order staying SFIO probe into nine companies related to Sahara group
news.para: The SFIO, a statutory corporate fraud investigating agency, had approached the top court against the December 13, 2021 order of the high court staying all subsequent actions and proceedings, including coercive measures and lookout notices, against the Sahara group chief and others.

news.title: CBI arrests ABIL group chairman in Yes Bank-DHFL scam case
news.para: The CBI suspects that illicit funds were routed through several real estate companies based in Maharashtra, they said. The agency had carried out searches at the premises of noted builders of the state on April 30 to further probe on this aspect of the case, they said.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's net profit falls to Rs 232.65 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 842.94 crore for the quarter under review as against Rs 800.87 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA to ask agency to check Nadaprabhu Kempegowda layout work
news.para: Looking into various petitions filed by legislators and citizens, the petition committee of the state legislature held a preliminary meeting with BDA officials on May 5.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board earns Rs 2 crore from four properties
news.para: The board had put total 35 freehold properties, including 29 residential and six commercial properties, for auction. The board found buyers for two EWS flats in sectors 40 and 52, selling them for Rs 22.5 lakh and Rs 24.5 lakh.
